progressive /prəˈɡrɛsɪv/

(progressives) 

1. ADJ Someone who is progressive or has progressive ideas has modern ideas about how things should be done, rather than traditional ones. 进步的 

例： ...a progressive businessman who had voted for Roosevelt in 1932 and 

1936. …在1932年和1936年投票支持罗斯福的一位进步商人。 

例： Willan was able to point to the progressive changes he had already introduced. 威兰能够指出他已经带来的有进步意义的变化。 

2. N-COUNT A progressive is someone who is progressive. 进步人士 

例： The Republicans were deeply split between progressives and conservatives. 共和党进步派和保守派之间分歧很大。 

3. ADJ A progressive change happens gradually over a period of time. 逐步的 

例： One prominent symptom of the disease is progressive loss of memory. 这种病的一个突出症状是记忆的逐步丧失。 

4. progressively ADV 逐步地 

例： Her symptoms became progressively worse. 她的症状逐步恶化。

</div>

